A5922 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-TEN-ACURA-NOTES-LADN     08-16 0297
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TEN-ACURA-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SANCHEZ VICARIO ON THE RUN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JOE STEVENS  
 c.1998 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   MANHATTAN BEACH, Calif. _ Arantxa Sanchez Vicario might lead the
women's tennis tour in nicknames.
</P>
<P>
   Sanchez Vicario is so renowned for her speed that Martina Hingis
dubbed her Forrest Gump, after the fleet-of-foot movie character.
</P>
<P>
   After her 6-4, 6-4 semifinal win in the Acura Classic over
Sanchez Vicario, Hingis noted that Sanchez Vicario's speed often
turns a match. ``You never know with her,'' Hingis said. ``She's a
big runner.''
</P>
<P>
   Other nicknames? Sanchez Vicario is also known as ``El Conejo,''
or the rabbit, or the ``Barcelona Bumblebee.''
</P>
<P>
   Handy competitor: Why has the 17-year-old Hingis held the top
ranking so firmly for more than a year? According to Sanchez
Vicario, it is not necessarily Hingis' ground strokes, serve or
athleticism. Rather, it's her quick hands, which give Hingis the
ability to create difficult shots.
</P>
<P>
   Four for four: When the top four seeds played in the semifinals
Saturday, it marked the fourth time this year that the top four
made it to the semifinals of a Corel WTA tour event.
</P>
<P>
   Upsets have been infrequent at Manhattan Beach, as only
sixth-seeded Irina Spirlea and seventh-seeded Sandrine Testud made
premature exits.
</P>
<P>
   Double your fun: Hingis has doubled her appearances in the
finals, as she and Natasha Zvereva advanced to the doubles final
with a 6-2, 6-3 win over Lori McNeil and Kimberly Po.
</P>
<P>
   After today's singles final, Hingis-Zvereva, the top-seeded team
in doubles, will meet either Chanda Rubin and Spirlea or Tamarine
Tanasugarn and Elena Tatarkova. The two unseeded doubles teams met
in the other semifinal late Saturday night. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-16-98 0019EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19980816.0008 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> MISCELLANEOUS TEXT (slug-filter) </DOCTYPE>
