<HEADLINE>
BOB SPRINGS LEAKS IN RAIN 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By THE ARIZONA REPUBLIC  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX - Heavy rains Saturday night caused problems at Bank One
Ballpark as rain leaked through the retractable roof.
</P>
<P>
   Diamondbacks President Rich Dozer said there was a small leak
above the stands on the first-base side, but it didn't cause any
fans to be displaced or problems with the game.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're more worried right now about a power outage,'' Dozer
said. ``We've been told there are large areas without power, and
the lights have flickered a couple of times.''
</P>
<P>
   However, one fan said the leak in the roof over Section 329
(left-field corner) was ``just gushing out'' and that the area
about 10 feet from the top row of the stadium was drenched. Fans in
that area said they filled out complaint cards to be compensated
for their discomfort.
</P>
<P>
   As guest relations staff members refused to comment on the leak,
water poured into their third-floor office. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
