<HEADLINE>
HYSAW COULD BE OUT FOR SEASON 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By PAOLA BOIVIN  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PAYSON, Ariz. _ Arizona State cornerback Courtney Hysaw
dislocated his right knee during practice at Camp Tontozona
Saturday and may be out for the season.
</P>
<P>
   Hysaw, a track standout from Denver who sat out last season,
fell during a drill. He was not hit by anyone. However, the field,
which has seen sporadic rain during the past few days, may have
given out under him.
</P>
<P>
   ``He was playing good,'' Bruce Snyder said. ``The whole thing is
unfortunate.''
</P>
<P>
   Hysaw was competing for a backup job behind starters Courtney
Jackson and J'Juan Cherry.
</P>
<P>
   ``It made me cry,'' Jackson said. ``I know how hard he worked. I
always told him I can't wait to see him play, to see him in
uniform.''
</P>
<P>
   Hysaw was taken by helicopter to Phoenix's Good Samaritan
Hospital. He is expected to undergo surgery in the next few days. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
