<HEADLINE>
EDITORS: 
</HEADLINE>
  
 August 16, 1998      The Hearst News Service will file these stories for Monday:
<TEXT>
<P>
   CLINTON-TESTIMONY (Washington) _ Almost seven months after he
promised to provide details about his relationship with Monica
Lewinsky, President Clinton faces the Kenneth Starr grand jury to
answer questions about that relationship. Later, he may make
televised remarks to the nation or issue a written statement. His
schedule calls for him to depart Monday for vacation at Martha's
Vineyard, Mass. By STEWART M. POWELL. (``w'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   MORSE-COLUMN (Undated) _ A whole lot of people in America think
they're having sex, but aren't. Don't panic. It's just a lawyers'
definition of sex that Bill Clinton may use to weasel out of lies
he told the American people about his relations with former White
House intern Monica Lewinsky. Imagine if, just once, he didn't play
games with words. He just might get away with telling the truth. By
ROB MORSE. (``k'' category.) (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   The Hearst News Service/Washington
</P>
