   SPORTS
</P>
<P>
   Second part of an Atlanta Journal Constitution series on life in
the minor leagues.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-GCLBRAVES _ ORLANDO, Fla. _ Team is based at the Braves'
spring camp at Disney World, but don't be fooled. Their is nothing
magical about this first stop in the minor leagues for most Braves
prospects. Games begin at noon under the blazing Florida sun. No
admission is charged, but a game is lucky to draw 10 fans. There is
that many countries represented on the Braves' 30-man roster.
English classes are held two nights a week. (Curtright, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
