</P>
<P>
   A sailor who traveled 5,000 miles across the sea and back had a
swallow tattooed on each side of his chest; a dragon tattoo denotes
that the sailor has traveled across the international line; the
names of ports are often tattooed on sailors' legs.
</P>
<P>
   A cross tattooed on the back of a British sailor was to spare
him from flogging; ``Hold Fast'' on the sailor's knuckles was a
safety reminder; propellers on the buttocks were supposed to keep
him afloat if the ship went down.
</P>
