<P>
   NIRELAND-BOMB (Omagh, Northern Ireland) _ The day after the
deadliest paramilitary attack in 29 years of sectarian violence in
this British province, dozens of people sat blank-faced or weeping
at a community center set up as a command post to find people still
missing. No group has claimed responsibility, but police and
political leaders, both Protestant and Catholic, say it appeared to
have been the work of a group calling itself the Real IRA, a
splinter group of the overwhelmingly Catholic Irish Republican
Army. By James F. Clarity. (Scheduled to move by 8 p.m. ET in ``i''
news file.) With map.
