<HEADLINE>
MOTHER WHO LEFT CHILDREN ALONE AT NIGHT IS ARRESTED 
</HEADLINE>
  (js) 
 By MICHAEL COOPER   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Alerted by a neighbor who spotted a dazed 3-year-old
boy wandering outside in the middle of the night, the police on
Sunday arrested a Brooklyn woman who they said left her six
children home alone while she went to a party Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   The mother, Samantha Stevens, 29, returned home from the party
around 5 a.m. Sunday and found police officers and child welfare
workers in her Bedford-Stuyvesant apartment. She was arrested and
charged with endangering the welfare of her children and with
possession of cocaine, said Theresa Farello, a department
spokeswoman.
</P>
<P>
   The children _ ranging in age from 5-month-old twin boys to an
11-year-old girl _ were discovered after the neighbor, Roslyn
Grahme, 41, looked out the window of her first-floor apartment at
709 Lafayette Ave. shortly after 3 a.m. and saw the 3-year-old boy,
clad only in diapers, walking by himself in a courtyard.
</P>
<P>
   ``He was just standing there shivering,'' she recalled. ``I
tried to give him some comfort. He wouldn't respond. He just kept
looking up.''
</P>
<P>
   Stevens was arrested on six counts of endangering the welfare of
a child and one count of drug possession, for a small amount of
cocaine found in her purse. The family had no prior history with
the Administration for Children's Services, said Leonora Wiener, an
agency spokeswoman.
</P>
<P>
   Ms. Stevens lived in a homeless shelter with the children before
she moved into her apartment in April, said a city official who
spoke on condition of anonymity. The official said Ms. Stevens told
the police that she had thought it was safe to leave the children
in bed when she went to the party around midnight.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
