<SLUG> BC-FBC-USCNOTE-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
USC LOOKS RAW IN SCRIMMAGE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVINE, Calif. _ As his first week of training camp concluded,
USC coach Paul Hackett couldn't help but say what he's been
thinking for several months.
</P>
<P>
   ``We are so young and inexperienced. It's painful almost, what
we have to go through,'' Hackett said. ``It'll be fine in a year or
two, but it doesn't help much now.''
</P>
<P>
   Hackett might be thinking long-term, but he was actually more
upbeat about the offense's meek performance in the opening
scrimmage Saturday, after having a day to review the tape.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was more pleased than I thought I would be,'' Hackett said.
``We had some good individual performances. We're just not in sync
as a group.''
</P>
<P>
   Hackett mentioned freshman tailback Frank Strong and offensive
linemen Jason Grain, Matt Welch and Travis Claridge as players who
stood out.
</P>
<P>
   He also liked freshman quarterback Jason Thomas, who saw his
most extensive action during the scrimmage.
</P>
<P>
   ``I thought Jason Thomas played the best he's played since he's
been here,'' Hackett said.
</P>
<P>
   __ Decision time: Hackett said he will decide by today or no
later than Tuesday who will back up starting quarterback Mike Van
Raaphorst for the Purdue game. Freshman Carson Palmer appears to be
the heavy favorite for the role.
</P>
<P>
   Several other starting positions, notably along the offensive
line, will probably be announced by midweek. Hackett said Grain is
getting close to locking up the starting position at left guard.
The center and right tackle positions also remain open.
</P>
<P>
   On defense, Ken Haslip seems ahead of Antuan Simmons at
cornerback, and Grant Pearsall is probably going to start ahead of
David Gibson at strong safety.
</P>
<P>
   __ Emergency punters: With freshman Mike MacGillivray the only
true punter, place kicker David Bell and wide receiver Mike
Bastianelli have been recruited as the backups.
</P>
<P>
   __ Injury report: Running back Sultan McCullough sat out
Sunday's practice with a sore hip. Offensive lineman Derek Graf of
Agoura has been bothered by a twisted knee for most of training
camp.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-16-98 2319EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
